Questions that can only be answered in a real jj+git colocated repo:

1. CREATE a colocated repo, write notes with mycelium.sh, then do
   jj amend / jj squash / jj rebase. Which notes survive? Which orphan?
   This is the ground truth — not docs, not assumptions.

2. BLOB STABILITY: edit a file, jj commit, add a note on the blob,
   then jj amend the commit message (no content change). Does the blob
   OID stay the same? Does the note survive?

3. TREE STABILITY: same test but for directory trees. Does jj amend
   change the tree OID even when file content is unchanged?

4. GIT HOOKS: do .git/hooks/pre-commit and pre-push fire when using
   jj commit / jj git push? Or are they bypassed?

5. ROUND-TRIP: write a note with mycelium.sh (git notes), then check
   if jj log shows any awareness of it. Then jj git push — do notes
   get pushed?

6. RESOLVE PATH: run 'git rev-parse HEAD:path' in a colocated repo
   after jj operations. Does HEAD stay in sync? Does jj's @ differ?

7. PERFORMANCE: does 'git notes list' slow down in repos where jj
   has created many rewritten commits? Hidden objects accumulate.
